The breakfast here is amazing and they have the best tasting home fries we have ever had. We decided to give here a try based on the recommendation of the doorman at our hotel since it's just a short walk from Brooklyn Heights Promenade which offer fantastic views of the Statue of Liberty and the city skyline.  We were seated very quickly on the patio and right away the staff were friendly and accommodating, especially as we came with our 1 year old son. The patio was nice and offered a quiet ambience especially since it was a Sunday.  We both had a spinach and avocado omelette which on the menu is a bacon and avocado omelette bit we subbed the bacon for spinach. It came with toast and the home fries it was delicious. The omelette was well cooked but not overcooked, it was quite smooth and tasty. The home fries were amazing and probably even better than the omelette - it was so flavourful that we both agreed that ketchup ruined the taste.  We will definitely revisit the next time we are in town.
